This project is a Python implementation of concepts and architecture originally
developed in CortexReach/memory-lancedb-pro, a TypeScript LanceDB memory plugin
for OpenClaw.

    https://github.com/CortexReach/memory-lancedb-pro

The following core ideas are derived from that work:

  - Hybrid BM25 + vector search with RRF fusion
  - Weibull composite decay scoring (recency × access frequency)
  - Tier management (core / working / peripheral) with automatic promotion
  - Supersede pattern for updates (archive-then-create, no in-place mutation)
  - Temporal classifier distinguishing static facts from time-sensitive phrases
  - Session compressor scoring conversation turns by signal value
  - Reflection layer for agent self-observation
  - AMAC admission-control gate (utility / confidence / novelty / recency)

